[00:00.54]Lesson 38 | 第38课
[00:02.41]Water and the traveller | 水与旅行者
[00:09.59]What does this text describe? | 本文描述了什么？
[00:13.50]Contamination of water supplies is usually due to poor sanitation close to water sources, | 供水污染通常是由于水源附近卫生条件差，
[00:21.30]sewage disposal into the sources themselves, leakage of sewage into distribution systems or contamination with industrial or farm waste. | 污水直接排入水源，污水泄漏进入分配系统，或受到工业或农业废物的污染。
[00:32.17]Even if a piped water supply is safe at its source, it is not always safe by the time it reaches the tap. | 即使管道供水在其源头是安全的，但当它到达水龙头时，也并非总是安全的。
[00:39.72]Intermittent tap-water supplies should be regarded as particularly suspect. | 间歇性自来水供应应被视为特别可疑。
[00:45.76]Travellers on short trips to areas with water supplies of uncertain quality | 短途旅行到水质不确定地区的旅行者
[00:51.08]should avoid drinking tap-water, or untreated water from any other source. | 应避免饮用自来水，或任何其他来源的未经处理的水。
[00:56.95]It is best to keep to hot drinks, bottled or canned drinks of well-known brand names-international standard of water treatment are usually followed at bottling plants. | 最好只喝热饮、知名品牌的瓶装或罐装饮料——瓶装厂通常会遵循国际水处理标准。
[01:08.27]Carbonated drinks are acidic, and slightly safer. | 碳酸饮料呈酸性，稍微安全一些。
[01:12.24]Make sure that all bottles are opened in your presence, and that their rims are clean and dry. | 确保所有瓶子都是在你面前打开的，并且瓶口清洁干燥。
[01:19.14]Boiling is always a good way of treating water. | 煮沸始终是处理水的好方法。
[01:22.36]Some hotels supply boiled water on request and this can be used for drinking, or for brushing teeth. | 有些酒店应要求提供开水，可用于饮用或刷牙。
[01:29.49]Portable boiling elements that can boil small quantities of water are useful when the right voltage of electricity is available. | 当有合适的电压时，能烧开少量水的便携式电热棒会很有用。
[01:37.86]Refuse politely any cold drink from an unknown source. | 礼貌地拒绝任何来源不明的冷饮。
[01:43.22]Ice is only as safe as the water from which it is made, | 冰的安全性取决于制作它的水，
[01:46.79]and should not be put in drinks unless it is known to be safe. | 除非已知其安全，否则不应将其放入饮料中。
[01:51.80]Drinks can be cooled by placing them on ice rather than adding ice to them. | 饮料可以通过放在冰块上冷却，而不是将冰块加入饮料中。
[01:58.17]Alcohol may be a medical disinfectant, but should not be relied upon to sterilize water. | 酒精可能是医用消毒剂，但不应指望它能给水消毒。
[02:05.57]Ethanol is more effective at a concentration of 50-70 percent; | 乙醇在50-70%的浓度下更有效；
[02:10.72]below 20 per cent, its bactericidal action is negligible. | 低于20%时，其杀菌作用微乎其微。
[02:15.91]Spirits labelled 95 proof contain only about 47 per cent alcohol. | 标示为95度的烈酒只含有大约47%的酒精。
[02:22.63]Beware of methylated alcohol, | 警惕工业酒精（甲醇变性酒精），
[02:24.89]which is very poisonous and should never be added to drinking water. | 它剧毒，绝不应加入饮用水中。
[02:30.71]If no other safe water supply can be obtained, | 如果无法获得其他安全水源，
[02:34.45]tap water that is too hot to touch can be left to cool and is generally safe to drink. | 热得烫手的自来水可以放凉后饮用，通常是安全的。
[02:41.50]Those planning a trip to remote areas, or intending to live in countries where drinking water is not readily available, | 计划去偏远地区旅行，或打算生活在饮用水不易获得的国家的人，
[02:49.29]should know about the various possible methods for making water safe. | 应该了解使水安全可饮用的各种可能方法。